This category of Mitigations describes a range of actions and technologies that can be implemented to prevent the spread of contagious diseases in green building neighborhoods and other infrastructure. These include the integration of new technologies such as digital PCR, biosensors, and IoT devices for monitoring and tracking. Contact tracing applications and mobile apps are also mentioned as tools for information dissemination and tracking. The use of IoT and AI, as well as interactive web apps and internet-based applications, is highlighted as ways to improve communication and access to information. Other measures include the implementation of touchless systems, smart meters and sensors, and the development of wearable devices for health monitoring. Additionally, the category includes mentions of mobile technology applications, Bluetooth contact tracing apps, and the integration of GIS and GPS applications. Overall, these Mitigations focus on leveraging technology and implementing various solutions to enhance disease prevention and control in green building neighborhoods and infrastructure environments.